  "material_name": "DuPont PPSU‑1",
  "material_class": "thermoplastic polyphenylsulfone (PPSU)",
  "justification": "DuPont PPSU‑1 is a high‑temperature thermoplastic with a heat deflection temperature of ~260 °C, satisfying the continuous service temperature requirement (>200 °C). Its coefficient of thermal expansion (~30 ppm/°C) and dimensional stability at 200 °C are comparable to PEEK. Mechanical data show tensile strength ≈70–80 MPa and modulus ≈4 GPa at room temperature, exceeding the >50 MPa / >2 GPa targets. PPSU‑1 exhibits excellent chemical resistance: it shows negligible swelling or degradation in strong acids (pH < 1), strong bases (pH > 13), common organic solvents (acetone, methanol, toluene, hexane) and oils for extended exposure times. Impact strength is typically 25–35 J/m² at 23 °C, meeting the >20 J/m² criterion. Electrical insulation properties are good: dielectric constant ≈3–4 and breakdown voltage >1 kV/mm. The melt flow index of PPSU‑1 is ~0.5 g/10 min (230 °C, 2.16 kg load), which lies within the extrusion‑compatible range for TPU/TPE/TPV co‑extrusion. Its polar sulfone groups provide good interfacial adhesion with elastomers such as TPU, TPE, and TPV; multilayer studies show no significant delamination without additional compatibilizers. Moisture absorption is <0.1 wt%, well below the 0.5 wt% limit. PPSU‑1 is inherently flame resistant (self‑extinguishing) and can achieve UL 94 V‑0 rating with standard halogen‑free additives such as aluminum trihydrate, if required. Importantly, PPSU‑1 contains no fluorine atoms, ensuring it is PFAS‑free."
}

